{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011xipoBfJaruqP5YUiN9SuM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import type { TestGenerationContext, CodebaseIntelligenceContext } from './types';\n     2→\n     3→export const TEST_SIGNATURE = `export async function test(page: Page, baseUrl: string, screenshotPath: string, stepLogger: any)`;\n     4→\n     5→export const MCP_SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You are an expert visual regression test engineer. Use Playwright MCP tools to EXPLORE pages and discover accurate selectors, then OUTPUT standard Playwright test code.\n     6→\n     7→MCP TOOLS: browser_navigate, browser_snapshot (accessibility tree + refs), browser_click, browser_type, browser_wait_for\n     8→\n     9→WORKFLOW: navigate → snapshot → interact with refs → snapshot to verify → identify reliable selectors → OUTPUT test code\n    10→\n    11→CRITICAL RULES:\n    12→- NEVER guess selectors — always verify via browser_snapshot first\n    13→- Element refs (e.g. \"ref=s2e5\") are for MCP exploration only, NOT for final test code\n    14→- Do NOT use browser_take_screenshot during exploration — screenshots go in the OUTPUT test code\n    15→\n    16→DYNAMIC ROUTES (e.g. /users/[id]):\n    17→Navigate to the parent list page first, snapshot to find links with real IDs, then navigate to the actual URL.\n    18→\n    19→CONSTRAINTS:\n    20→- Use baseUrl for navigation (no hardcoded URLs)\n    21→- Capture at least one screenshot using screenshotPath\n    22→- Export async function \"test\" with exact signature: ${TEST_SIGNATURE}\n    23→- Do NOT use \\`import\\` — \\`expect\\`, \\`page\\`, \\`baseUrl\\`, \\`screenshotPath\\`, \\`stepLogger\\` are provided by the runner\n    24→- expect matchers: toBe, toEqual, toBeTruthy, toBeFalsy, toContain, toHaveLength, toMatch, toMatchObject, toHaveURL, toHaveTitle, toBeVisible, toBeHidden, toHaveText, toContainText, toHaveAttribute, toHaveCount, toBeEnabled, toBeDisabled, toBeChecked, toHaveValue (all support .not)\n    25→- Never mix regex text and CSS selectors in one locator — use page.getByText(/pattern/i) for regex, page.locator('[attr=\"x\"]') for CSS\n    26→\n    27→FINAL OUTPUT: After exploration, generate standard Playwright test code using discovered selectors.\n    28→\n    29→\\`\\`\\`typescript\n    30→import { Page } from 'playwright';\n    31→\n    32→${TEST_SIGNATURE} {\n    33→  stepLogger.log('Navigating to page');\n    34→  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`);\n    35→  await page.locator('[data-testid=\"discovered-element\"]').click();\n    36→  stepLogger.log('Taking screenshot');\n    37→  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true });\n    38→}\n    39→\\`\\`\\``;\n    40→\n    41→export const SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You generate Playwright visual regression tests. Output ONLY a JavaScript code block.\n    42→\n    43→RULES:\n    44→- Plain JavaScript, NO TypeScript, NO imports\n    45→- Signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n    46→- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n    47→- Wait: await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n    48→- URL assert: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n    49→- Visibility: await expect(page.locator('body')).toBeVisible()\n    50→- Screenshot: await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true })\n    51→- Log: stepLogger.log('message')\n    52→\n    53→SYNTAX — CRITICAL:\n    54→- WRONG: const el: Locator = page.locator(...) → RIGHT: const el = page.locator(...)\n    55→- WRONG: import { expect } from '@playwright/test' → RIGHT: (no imports — expect is a parameter)\n    56→- WRONG: (page: Page, baseUrl: string) → RIGHT: (page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n    57→- Every statement must end with a semicolon or closing brace\n    58→- Every variable declaration must use const or let\n    59→- Verify all brackets/parens are balanced before outputting\n    60→\n    61→ASSERTIONS — prefer resilient checks:\n    62→- Use toContainText() over exact toHaveText() when possible\n    63→- Use toBeTruthy() only on values you are certain exist\n    64→- Prefer toBeVisible() for element presence checks\n    65→- If checking a count, use toHaveCount() with the expected number, not toBeTruthy()\n    66→\n    67→EXAMPLE (static route):\n    68→\\`\\`\\`javascript\n    69→export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger) {\n    70→  stepLogger.log('Navigate');\n    71→  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/settings\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });\n    72→  await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n    73→  await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/settings/);\n    74→  await expect(page.locator('body')).toBeVisible();\n    75→  stepLogger.log('Screenshot');\n    76→  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true });\n    77→}\n    78→\\`\\`\\`\n    79→\n    80→EXAMPLE (dynamic route — discover real ID from list page):\n    81→\\`\\`\\`javascript\n    82→export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger) {\n    83→  stepLogger.log('Navigate to list page to find a real item');\n    84→  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/tests\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });\n    85→  await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n    86→  const firstLink = page.locator('a[href*=\"/tests/\"]').first();\n    87→  await expect(firstLink).toBeVisible();\n    88→  const href = await firstLink.getAttribute('href');\n    89→  stepLogger.log('Navigate to detail page');\n    90→  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}\\${href}\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });\n    91→  await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n    92→  await expect(page.locator('body')).toBeVisible();\n    93→  stepLogger.log('Screenshot');\n    94→  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true });\n    95→}\n    96→\\`\\`\\``;\n    97→\n    98→export function createTestPrompt(context: TestGenerationContext): string {\n    99→  const parts: string[] = [];\n   100→\n   101→  if (context.useMCP) {\n   102→    parts.push('Use MCP tools to explore the page, then generate standard Playwright test code.');\n   103→\n   104→    if (context.userPrompt) {\n   105→      parts.push(`\\nTest objective: ${context.userPrompt}`);\n   106→    }\n   107→\n   108→    if (context.targetUrl || context.routePath) {\n   109→      const route = context.targetUrl || context.routePath;\n   110→      parts.push(`\\nTarget: ${route}`);\n   111→\n   112→      if (context.isDynamicRoute) {\n   113→        parts.push(`\\nThis is a DYNAMIC route with parameters. You MUST:`);\n   114→        parts.push(`1. First browser_navigate to a parent/list page`);\n   115→        parts.push(`2. Use browser_snapshot to find links with actual IDs`);\n   116→        parts.push(`3. Navigate to discovered URL with real parameters`);\n   117→\n   118→        if (context.siblingRoutes?.length) {\n   119→          parts.push(`\\nRelated routes that may help find real data: ${context.siblingRoutes.join(', ')}`);\n   120→        }\n   121→      }\n   122→    }\n   123→\n   124→    // Add scan context if available\n   125→    if (context.scanContext) {\n   126→      parts.push(buildScanContextSection(context.scanContext));\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    // Add codebase intelligence if available\n   130→    if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n   131→      parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n   132→    }\n   133→\n   134→    parts.push(`\\nWorkflow: navigate → snapshot → explore → OUTPUT Playwright test code with discovered selectors`);\n   135→    return parts.join('\\n');\n   136→  }\n   137→\n   138→  parts.push('Generate a Playwright visual regression test.');\n   139→\n   140→  if (context.userPrompt) {\n   141→    parts.push(`\\nTest objective: ${context.userPrompt}`);\n   142→  }\n   143→\n   144→  if (context.targetUrl || context.routePath) {\n   145→    const route = context.targetUrl || context.routePath;\n   146→    parts.push(`\\nTarget: ${route}`);\n   147→\n   148→    if (context.isDynamicRoute) {\n   149→      parts.push(`\\nIMPORTANT: This is a dynamic route. Before testing it directly:`);\n   150→      parts.push(`1. Navigate to the parent list page first (e.g., for /users/[id], go to /users)`);\n   151→      parts.push(`2. Wait for the list to load and find a valid link`);\n   152→      parts.push(`3. Click the link or extract the href to get a real ID`);\n   153→      parts.push(`4. Then test the actual page with real data`);\n   154→\n   155→      if (context.siblingRoutes?.length) {\n   156→        parts.push(`\\nRelated routes: ${context.siblingRoutes.join(', ')}`);\n   157→      }\n   158→    }\n   159→  }\n   160→\n   161→  // Add scan context if available\n   162→  if (context.scanContext) {\n   163→    parts.push(buildScanContextSection(context.scanContext));\n   164→  }\n   165→\n   166→  // Add codebase intelligence if available\n   167→  if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n   168→    parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n   169→  }\n   170→\n   171→  if (context.availableRoutes?.length) {\n   172→    parts.push(`\\n--- Available Routes (ONLY navigate to these) ---`);\n   173→    parts.push(context.availableRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n'));\n   174→    parts.push(`\\nCRITICAL: Do NOT invent or guess URLs. ONLY use routes from the list above.`);\n   175→    parts.push(`If the test objective refers to a page not in this list, navigate to the closest matching route.`);\n   176→  }\n   177→\n   178→  // Add guidelines and requirements sections\n   179→  parts.push(`\n   180→--- Requirements ---\n   181→- Plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n   182→- Signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n   183→- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n   184→- URL checks: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n   185→- Content checks: await expect(page.locator('body')).toBeVisible()\n   186→- Screenshot: await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true })\n   187→- Log actions: stepLogger.log('message')\n   188→\n   189→Return ONLY the code block, no explanations.`);\n   190→\n   191→  return parts.join('\\n');\n   192→}\n   193→\n   194→function buildScanContextSection(scanContext: import('./types').ScanContext): string {\n   195→  const lines: string[] = ['\\n--- Discovery Context ---'];\n   196→\n   197→  // Add source-specific context\n   198→  if (scanContext.discoverySource === 'nav-link' && scanContext.navLabel) {\n   199→    lines.push(`This route appears in navigation as \"${scanContext.navLabel}\".`);\n   200→    lines.push('Verify the page matches its navigation label purpose.');\n   201→  }\n   202→\n   203→  if (scanContext.discoverySource === 'spec-analysis' && scanContext.specDescription) {\n   204→    lines.push(`From specification: ${scanContext.specDescription}`);\n   205→    lines.push('Test the documented behavior.');\n   206→  }\n   207→\n   208→  if (scanContext.discoverySource === 'file-scan' && scanContext.sourceFilePath) {\n   209→    lines.push(`Source file: ${scanContext.sourceFilePath}`);\n   210→  }\n   211→\n   212→  // Add framework hint\n   213→  if (scanContext.framework) {\n   214→    lines.push(`Framework: ${scanContext.framework}`);\n   215→  }\n   216→\n   217→  // Add router type if relevant\n   218→  if (scanContext.routerType) {\n   219→    lines.push(`Router: ${scanContext.routerType}`);\n   220→  }\n   221→\n   222→  // Add test suggestions as scenarios to consider\n   223→  if (scanContext.testSuggestions && scanContext.testSuggestions.length > 0) {\n   224→    lines.push('\\nSuggested scenarios to consider:');\n   225→    for (const suggestion of scanContext.testSuggestions) {\n   226→      lines.push(`- ${suggestion}`);\n   227→    }\n   228→  }\n   229→\n   230→  // Add functional area context\n   231→  if (scanContext.functionalAreaName) {\n   232→    lines.push(`\\nFunctional area: ${scanContext.functionalAreaName}`);\n   233→    if (scanContext.functionalAreaDescription) {\n   234→      lines.push(`Context: ${scanContext.functionalAreaDescription}`);\n   235→    }\n   236→  }\n   237→\n   238→  return lines.join('\\n');\n   239→}\n   240→\n   241→function buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(intel: CodebaseIntelligenceContext): string {\n   242→  const lines: string[] = ['\\n--- Project Intelligence ---'];\n   243→\n   244→  if (intel.framework) lines.push(`Framework: ${intel.framework}`);\n   245→  if (intel.cssFramework) lines.push(`CSS: ${intel.cssFramework}`);\n   246→  if (intel.selectorStrategy) lines.push(`Selector strategy: ${intel.selectorStrategy}`);\n   247→  if (intel.authMechanism && intel.authMechanism !== 'none detected') {\n   248→    lines.push(`Auth: ${intel.authMechanism} — protected routes may redirect to login`);\n   249→  }\n   250→  if (intel.stateManagement) lines.push(`State management: ${intel.stateManagement}`);\n   251→  if (intel.apiLayer) lines.push(`API layer: ${intel.apiLayer}`);\n   252→  if (intel.projectDescription) lines.push(`App: ${intel.projectDescription}`);\n   253→\n   254→  if (intel.testingRecommendations && intel.testingRecommendations.length > 0) {\n   255→    lines.push('\\nTesting recommendations:');\n   256→    for (const rec of intel.testingRecommendations.slice(0, 8)) {\n   257→      lines.push(`- ${rec}`);\n   258→    }\n   259→  }\n   260→\n   261→  return lines.join('\\n');\n   262→}\n   263→\n   264→export function createFixPrompt(context: TestGenerationContext): string {\n   265→  const parts: string[] = [`Fix this failing Playwright test.\n   266→\n   267→Original test code:\n   268→\\`\\`\\`typescript\n   269→${context.existingCode}\n   270→\\`\\`\\`\n   271→\n   272→Error message:\n   273→${context.errorMessage}`];\n   274→\n   275→  if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n   276→    parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n   277→  }\n   278→\n   279→  if (context.availableRoutes?.length) {\n   280→    parts.push(`\\nAvailable Routes (ONLY use these in page.goto()):`);\n   281→    parts.push(context.availableRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n'));\n   282→    parts.push(`If the current page.goto() URL is not in this list, change it to the closest matching route.`);\n   283→  }\n   284→\n   285→  parts.push(`\n   286→ERROR DIAGNOSIS — identify the category FIRST, then apply the matching fix strategy:\n   287→- \"Unexpected identifier\" or \"Unexpected token\" → SYNTAX ERROR: Look for missing commas, semicolons, or unmatched brackets. Remove any TypeScript annotations (: Type, as Type). Remove any import statements.\n   288→- \"404\" or \"not found\" → WRONG URL: The page.goto() URL doesn't exist. Change it to a route from the available routes list.\n   289→- \"timeout\" or \"waiting for selector\" → SELECTOR MISMATCH: The element doesn't exist with that selector. Use broader selectors (getByRole, getByText) or remove the assertion.\n   290→- \"X is not a function\" → INVALID API: Using a non-existent method. Check expect() matcher names and Playwright API.\n   291→- \"Expected\" + \"Received\" → ASSERTION FAILURE: The page content doesn't match expectations. Loosen the assertion or use a more flexible match (toContain instead of toBe, regex instead of exact string).\n   292→- \"login\" or \"redirect\" or \"sign-in\" → AUTH ISSUE: Add auth state check — if (page.url().includes('/login')) return;\n   293→- \"net::ERR\" or \"ERR_CONNECTION\" → NETWORK ERROR: The server may not be ready. Add waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded').\n   294→\n   295→Instructions:\n   296→1. Identify which error category above matches the error message\n   297→2. Apply ONLY the minimal fix for that category — do not rewrite the entire test\n   298→3. Verify your fix actually changes something (not identical to input)\n   299→\n   300→Rules:\n   301→- Write plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript type annotations (no \": Page\", no \": string\", no \": any\")\n   302→- Do NOT use \\`import\\` — expect is provided by the runner\n   303→- ALWAYS use regex for URL checks: await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/); — never exact string URLs\n   304→- Never mix regex text and CSS selectors in one locator — use page.getByText(/pattern/i) for regex\n   305→\n   306→Return ONLY the fixed code, no explanations.`);\n   307→\n   308→  return parts.join('\\n');\n   309→}\n   310→\n   311→export function createMcpFixPrompt(context: TestGenerationContext): string {\n   312→  return `Fix this failing Playwright test by exploring the live page with MCP tools.\n   313→\n   314→Original test code:\n   315→\\`\\`\\`typescript\n   316→${context.existingCode}\n   317→\\`\\`\\`\n   318→\n   319→Error message:\n   320→${context.errorMessage}\n   321→\n   322→Target URL: ${context.targetUrl || 'unknown'}\n   323→\n   324→Instructions:\n   325→- browser_navigate to the target URL, then browser_snapshot to see current page structure\n   326→- Compare actual page selectors/content with the failing test to identify what changed\n   327→- Fix the test using discovered selectors; maintain the same function signature and intent\n   328→- Write plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript type annotations, NO imports\n   329→- ALWAYS use regex for URL checks: await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/);\n   330→- Use only valid matchers (toBe, toEqual, toBeTruthy, toBeFalsy, toContain, toMatch, toHaveURL, toHaveTitle, toBeVisible, toHaveText, toContainText, toHaveAttribute, toHaveCount, etc.)\n   331→- Never mix regex text and CSS selectors in one locator — use page.getByText(/pattern/i) for regex\n   332→\n   333→Return ONLY the fixed code, no explanations.`;\n   334→}\n   335→\n   336→export function createEnhancePrompt(context: TestGenerationContext): string {\n   337→  const parts: string[] = [];\n   338→\n   339→  parts.push(`Enhance this Playwright visual regression test:\n   340→\n   341→Current test code:\n   342→\\`\\`\\`typescript\n   343→${context.existingCode}\n   344→\\`\\`\\``);\n   345→\n   346→  if (context.userPrompt) {\n   347→    parts.push(`\\nEnhancement request: ${context.userPrompt}`);\n   348→  } else {\n   349→    parts.push(`\\nEnhancements to make:\n   350→- Add more assertions to verify page state\n   351→- Improve selector reliability\n   352→- Add checks for common edge cases\n   353→- Improve logging with stepLogger\n   354→- Add waits for dynamic content`);\n   355→  }\n   356→\n   357→  parts.push(`\\nReturn ONLY the enhanced code, no explanations.`);\n   358→\n   359→  return parts.join('\\n');\n   360→}\n   361→\n   362→export function createRouteScanPrompt(codebaseContext: string, repoFullName?: string, intelligence?: CodebaseIntelligenceContext): string {\n   363→  const repoLine = repoFullName ? `\\nRepository: ${repoFullName}\\n` : '';\n   364→  const intelSection = intelligence ? buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(intelligence) : '';\n   365→  return `Analyze this codebase structure and identify all testable routes/pages.\n   366→${repoLine}${intelSection}\n   367→Codebase context:\n   368→${codebaseContext}\n   369→\n   370→Return a JSON object with a flat array of routes:\n   371→{\n   372→  \"routes\": [\n   373→    {\n   374→      \"path\": \"/users\",\n   375→      \"type\": \"static\",\n   376→      \"functionalArea\": \"User Management\",\n   377→      \"description\": \"User listing page\",\n   378→      \"testSuggestions\": [\"Verify user list loads\", \"Check pagination\"]\n   379→    },\n   380→    {\n   381→      \"path\": \"/users/[id]\",\n   382→      \"type\": \"dynamic\",\n   383→      \"functionalArea\": \"User Management\",\n   384→      \"description\": \"User profile page\",\n   385→      \"testSuggestions\": [\"Test with valid user ID\", \"Test error state for invalid ID\"]\n   386→    },\n   387→    {\n   388→      \"path\": \"/dashboard\",\n   389→      \"type\": \"static\",\n   390→      \"functionalArea\": \"Dashboard\",\n   391→      \"description\": \"Main dashboard page\",\n   392→      \"testSuggestions\": [\"Verify dashboard loads\", \"Check metric widgets\"]\n   393→    }\n   394→  ]\n   395→}\n   396→\n   397→Guidelines:\n   398→- Include all user-facing pages that benefit from visual regression testing\n   399→- Mark routes as \"static\" or \"dynamic\" based on URL parameters\n   400→- Use \"functionalArea\" to label the logical group (e.g. \"Authentication\", \"Settings\")\n   401→- Provide brief test suggestions for each route\n   402→\n   403→Return ONLY the JSON object, no explanations.`;\n   404→}\n   405→\n   406→export function createCodeDiffScanPrompt(\n   407→  changedFilesContext: string,\n   408→  baseBranch: string,\n   409→  headBranch: string,\n   410→  repoFullName?: string\n   411→): string {\n   412→  const repoNote = repoFullName ? `\\nRepository: ${repoFullName}` : '';\n   413→  return `You are analyzing code changes between two git branches to identify what visual regression tests should be created to cover the specific changes.\n   414→${repoNote}\n   415→Base branch: ${baseBranch}\n   416→Head branch: ${headBranch}\n   417→\n   418→Changed files and their contents:\n   419→${changedFilesContext}\n   420→\n   421→Analyze the actual code changes above and identify:\n   422→1. What specific functionality was added or modified\n   423→2. Which user-facing pages/routes are affected by these changes\n   424→3. What specific behaviors should be tested based on the diff\n   425→\n   426→For each affected route, generate test suggestions that target the EXACT changes — not generic page checks. For example:\n   427→- If a new button was added → \"Test the new [button name] button click behavior\"\n   428→- If form validation changed → \"Verify updated validation rules for [field]\"\n   429→- If a component was restyled → \"Check visual appearance of [component] after style changes\"\n   430→- If a new page was added → \"Test the new [page] route renders correctly with expected elements\"\n   431→\n   432→Return a JSON object with this exact structure:\n   433→{\n   434→  \"functionalAreas\": [\n   435→    {\n   436→      \"name\": \"Area Name\",\n   437→      \"description\": \"Brief description of what changed in this area\",\n   438→      \"routes\": [\n   439→        {\n   440→          \"path\": \"/affected-route\",\n   441→          \"type\": \"static\",\n   442→          \"description\": \"What changed on this page\",\n   443→          \"testSuggestions\": [\"Specific test targeting the actual code change\"]\n   444→        }\n   445→      ]\n   446→    }\n   447→  ]\n   448→}\n   449→\n   450→Guidelines:\n   451→- Group changes under logical functional areas based on what was modified\n   452→- Only include routes that are actually affected by the code changes\n   453→- Test suggestions MUST reference the specific change, not generic \"verify page loads\"\n   454→- Mark routes as \"static\" or \"dynamic\" based on URL parameters\n   455→- For dynamic routes, use bracket notation: /users/[id]\n   456→- If changes are purely backend/non-visual, still suggest routes where the effects would be visible\n   457→\n   458→Return ONLY the JSON object, no explanations or markdown formatting.`;\n   459→}\n   460→\n   461→export function createSpecAnalysisPrompt(specContent: string): string {\n   462→  return `Analyze the following specification/documentation content and extract functional areas, routes, and test scenarios.\n   463→\n   464→Specification content:\n   465→${specContent}\n   466→\n   467→Return a JSON object with this exact structure:\n   468→{\n   469→  \"functionalAreas\": [\n   470→    {\n   471→      \"name\": \"Area Name\",\n   472→      \"description\": \"Brief description of this functional area\",\n   473→      \"routes\": [\n   474→        {\n   475→          \"path\": \"/example-path\",\n   476→          \"type\": \"static\",\n   477→          \"description\": \"What this route does\"\n   478→        }\n   479→      ]\n   480→    }\n   481→  ],\n   482→  \"testScenarios\": [\n   483→    {\n   484→      \"route\": \"/example-path\",\n   485→      \"suggestions\": [\"Test scenario 1\", \"Test scenario 2\"]\n   486→    }\n   487→  ]\n   488→}\n   489→\n   490→Guidelines:\n   491→- Group related routes under logical functional areas\n   492→- Route type should be \"static\" or \"dynamic\" (dynamic routes have parameters like [id])\n   493→- For dynamic routes, use bracket notation: /users/[id]\n   494→- Test scenarios should be actionable visual regression test descriptions\n   495→- Focus on user-facing pages that benefit from visual testing\n   496→- Extract as many meaningful routes and test scenarios as possible from the spec\n   497→\n   498→Return ONLY the JSON object, no explanations or markdown formatting.`;\n   499→}\n   500→\n   501→export function createMCPExploreRoutesPrompt(baseURL: string, existingRoutes: string[], intelligence?: CodebaseIntelligenceContext): string {\n   502→  const seedSection = existingRoutes.length > 0\n   503→    ? `\\nAlready known routes (use as seed starting points to explore deeper):\\n${existingRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n')}`\n   504→    : '';\n   505→  const intelSection = intelligence ? buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(intelligence) : '';\n   506→\n   507→  return `You are exploring a live web application to discover all available routes/pages.\n   508→\n   509→Base URL: ${baseURL}\n   510→${seedSection}${intelSection}\n   511→\n   512→EXPLORATION INSTRUCTIONS:\n   513→1. Navigate to ${baseURL} and snapshot to find navigation links, sidebars, menus\n   514→2. Click through discovered links and record each unique URL pathname\n   515→3. Look for sub-navigation, tabs, or nested links on each page\n   516→4. Visit any known routes listed above as additional starting points\n   517→5. Note whether each route is static or dynamic (has IDs/slugs in the URL)\n   518→\n   519→IMPORTANT:\n   520→- Only record routes belonging to this application (same origin as baseURL)\n   521→- Convert dynamic segments to bracket notation (e.g., /users/123 → /users/[id])\n   522→- Do NOT include hash fragments, query parameters, or external links\n   523→\n   524→Return a flat JSON array of discovered routes:\n   525→\\`\\`\\`json\n   526→{\n   527→  \"routes\": [\n   528→    {\"path\": \"/dashboard\", \"type\": \"static\", \"functionalArea\": \"Dashboard\", \"description\": \"Main dashboard page\", \"testSuggestions\": [\"Verify dashboard loads correctly\", \"Check navigation elements\"]},\n   529→    {\"path\": \"/users/[id]\", \"type\": \"dynamic\", \"functionalArea\": \"User Management\", \"description\": \"User profile page\", \"testSuggestions\": [\"Test with valid user ID\", \"Test error state for invalid ID\"]}\n   530→  ]\n   531→}\n   532→\\`\\`\\`\n   533→\n   534→Use \"functionalArea\" to label the logical group for each route (e.g. \"Authentication\", \"Settings\").\n   535→\n   536→Return ONLY the JSON object inside a code block, no other text.`;\n   537→}\n   538→\n   539→export function createUserStoryExtractionPrompt(specContent: string): string {\n   540→  return `Analyze the following specification/requirements document and extract all User Stories (US) and their Acceptance Criteria (AC).\n   541→\n   542→Document content:\n   543→${specContent}\n   544→\n   545→Extract User Stories and Acceptance Criteria with the following rules:\n   546→1. Each distinct feature or capability should be its own User Story\n   547→2. Each User Story should have clear, testable Acceptance Criteria\n   548→3. Group related ACs under the same User Story\n   549→4. Provide a descriptive name for each AC that works as a test name\n   550→\n   551→Format your response as markdown using this exact structure:\n   552→\n   553→### User Story 1: [Functional area name]\n   554→**As a** [role]\n   555→**I want to** [feature/capability]\n   556→**So that** [benefit/value]\n   557→\n   558→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   559→- AC1: [Clear, testable criterion that describes expected behavior]\n   560→- AC2: [Another criterion]\n   561→\n   562→### User Story 2: [Next functional area]\n   563→...\n   564→\n   565→Guidelines:\n   566→- User Story titles should be concise functional area names (e.g., \"User Authentication\", \"Dashboard Analytics\")\n   567→- Each AC MUST describe a specific, observable user action and expected system response that can be verified in a browser\n   568→- DO NOT include: questions, suggestions, meta-commentary, implementation tasks, or vague criteria\n   569→- DO NOT include ACs like \"Create additional tests...\", \"Consider...\", \"Should we...\", \"Implement...\", \"Ensure proper...\"\n   570→- Bad AC: \"Ensure proper error handling\" (vague, not testable)\n   571→- Good AC: \"When user submits login form with wrong password, an error message 'Invalid credentials' appears\"\n   572→- Each AC should be independently testable in a browser-based visual regression test\n   573→- If a requirement is not testable via browser interaction, skip it\n   574→- If the document doesn't follow formal US/AC format, infer them from the requirements`;\n   575→}\n   576→\n   577→export function createBranchAwareTestPrompt(context: {\n   578→  testName: string;\n   579→  acceptanceCriteria: string;\n   580→  userStoryTitle: string;\n   581→  userStoryDescription: string;\n   582→  targetUrl?: string;\n   583→  branchChanges?: {\n   584→    changedFiles: string[];\n   585→    fileDiffs?: string;\n   586→  };\n   587→  codebaseIntelligence?: CodebaseIntelligenceContext;\n   588→  availableRoutes?: string[];\n   589→}): string {\n   590→  const parts: string[] = [];\n   591→\n   592→  parts.push(`Generate a Playwright visual regression test for the following acceptance criterion.\n   593→\n   594→User Story: ${context.userStoryTitle}\n   595→${context.userStoryDescription}\n   596→\n   597→Acceptance Criterion: ${context.acceptanceCriteria}\n   598→Test Name: ${context.testName}`);\n   599→\n   600→  if (context.targetUrl) {\n   601→    parts.push(`\\nTarget URL: ${context.targetUrl}`);\n   602→  }\n   603→\n   604→  if (context.branchChanges) {\n   605→    parts.push(`\\n--- Branch Code Context ---`);\n   606→    parts.push(`The following files have been changed in the branch:`);\n   607→    for (const file of context.branchChanges.changedFiles) {\n   608→      parts.push(`- ${file}`);\n   609→    }\n   610→    if (context.branchChanges.fileDiffs) {\n   611→      parts.push(`\\nRelevant code changes:\\n${context.branchChanges.fileDiffs}`);\n   612→    }\n   613→    parts.push(`\\nUse this context to write more accurate selectors and assertions based on the actual code changes.`);\n   614→  }\n   615→\n   616→  if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n   617→    parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n   618→  }\n   619→\n   620→  if (context.availableRoutes?.length) {\n   621→    parts.push(`\\n--- Available Routes (ONLY navigate to these) ---`);\n   622→    parts.push(context.availableRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n'));\n   623→    parts.push(`\\nCRITICAL: Do NOT invent or guess URLs. ONLY use routes from the list above.`);\n   624→    parts.push(`If the acceptance criterion refers to a page not in this list, navigate to the closest matching route and test what is available there.`);\n   625→  }\n   626→\n   627→  parts.push(`\n   628→--- Guidelines ---\n   629→- Write the test to verify the acceptance criterion\n   630→- Use descriptive stepLogger.log() messages matching the AC steps\n   631→- Add assertions that verify the expected behavior\n   632→- Capture screenshots at meaningful states\n   633→- Handle loading states for stable screenshots\n   634→\n   635→DYNAMIC ROUTES (paths with [id], [slug], etc.):\n   636→- First navigate to the parent list page (e.g., for /tests/[id], go to /tests)\n   637→- Wait for the page to load, then find a link or row in the list\n   638→- Click the first item or extract its href to get a real URL with an actual ID\n   639→- Then test the detail page with real data\n   640→- NEVER hardcode fake IDs like \"123\" or \"test-id\"\n   641→\n   642→SELECTORS (this app uses shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS):\n   643→- Buttons: page.getByRole('button', { name: '...' })\n   644→- Inputs: page.getByRole('textbox') or page.getByLabel('...')\n   645→- Tabs: page.getByRole('tab', { name: '...' })\n   646→- Dialog: page.getByRole('dialog')\n   647→- Links: page.getByRole('link', { name: '...' })\n   648→- Headings: page.getByRole('heading', { name: '...' })\n   649→- Prefer getByRole/getByText/getByLabel over CSS selectors\n   650→\n   651→LOADING STATES:\n   652→- After navigation: await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n   653→- Before assertions: allow time for dynamic content to render\n   654→- For async data: await page.locator('[data-loading]').waitFor({ state: 'hidden', timeout: 5000 }).catch(() => {})\n   655→\n   656→--- Requirements ---\n   657→- Plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n   658→- Function signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n   659→- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n   660→- URL checks: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n   661→- At least one screenshot must be captured\n   662→- Use baseUrl parameter for navigation\n   663→- ASSERTIONS: prefer toBeVisible() for element checks, toContainText() for text, regex toHaveURL() for URLs\n   664→- NEVER use toBeTruthy() on a value that might not exist — use toBeVisible() on the locator instead\n   665→\n   666→Return ONLY the code block, no explanations.`);\n   667→\n   668→  return parts.join('\\n');\n   669→}\n   670→\n   671→export function extractCodeFromResponse(response: string): string {\n   672→  // Try to extract code from markdown code blocks\n   673→  const codeBlockMatch = response.match(/```(?:typescript|ts|javascript|js)?\\n([\\s\\S]*?)```/);\n   674→  if (codeBlockMatch) {\n   675→    return codeBlockMatch[1].trim();\n   676→  }\n   677→\n   678→  // If no code block, check if response starts with import or export\n   679→  if (response.trim().startsWith('import') || response.trim().startsWith('export')) {\n   680→    return response.trim();\n   681→  }\n   682→\n   683→  // Return as-is if we can't extract\n   684→  return response.trim();\n   685→}\n   686→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"73c78856-d8a6-4cc9-9d03-e1f1ae524099","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ewyct/dev/lastest2/src/lib/ai/prompts.ts","content":"import type { TestGenerationContext, CodebaseIntelligenceContext } from './types';\n\nexport const TEST_SIGNATURE = `export async function test(page: Page, baseUrl: string, screenshotPath: string, stepLogger: any)`;\n\nexport const MCP_SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You are an expert visual regression test engineer. Use Playwright MCP tools to EXPLORE pages and discover accurate selectors, then OUTPUT standard Playwright test code.\n\nMCP TOOLS: browser_navigate, browser_snapshot (accessibility tree + refs), browser_click, browser_type, browser_wait_for\n\nWORKFLOW: navigate → snapshot → interact with refs → snapshot to verify → identify reliable selectors → OUTPUT test code\n\nCRITICAL RULES:\n- NEVER guess selectors — always verify via browser_snapshot first\n- Element refs (e.g. \"ref=s2e5\") are for MCP exploration only, NOT for final test code\n- Do NOT use browser_take_screenshot during exploration — screenshots go in the OUTPUT test code\n\nDYNAMIC ROUTES (e.g. /users/[id]):\nNavigate to the parent list page first, snapshot to find links with real IDs, then navigate to the actual URL.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Use baseUrl for navigation (no hardcoded URLs)\n- Capture at least one screenshot using screenshotPath\n- Export async function \"test\" with exact signature: ${TEST_SIGNATURE}\n- Do NOT use \\`import\\` — \\`expect\\`, \\`page\\`, \\`baseUrl\\`, \\`screenshotPath\\`, \\`stepLogger\\` are provided by the runner\n- expect matchers: toBe, toEqual, toBeTruthy, toBeFalsy, toContain, toHaveLength, toMatch, toMatchObject, toHaveURL, toHaveTitle, toBeVisible, toBeHidden, toHaveText, toContainText, toHaveAttribute, toHaveCount, toBeEnabled, toBeDisabled, toBeChecked, toHaveValue (all support .not)\n- Never mix regex text and CSS selectors in one locator — use page.getByText(/pattern/i) for regex, page.locator('[attr=\"x\"]') for CSS\n\nFINAL OUTPUT: After exploration, generate standard Playwright test code using discovered selectors.\n\n\\`\\`\\`typescript\nimport { Page } from 'playwright';\n\n${TEST_SIGNATURE} {\n  stepLogger.log('Navigating to page');\n  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`);\n  await page.locator('[data-testid=\"discovered-element\"]').click();\n  stepLogger.log('Taking screenshot');\n  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true });\n}\n\\`\\`\\``;\n\nexport const SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You generate Playwright visual regression tests. Output ONLY a JavaScript code block.\n\nRULES:\n- Plain JavaScript, NO TypeScript, NO imports\n- Signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n- Wait: await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n- URL assert: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n- Visibility: await expect(page.locator('body')).toBeVisible()\n- Screenshot: await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true })\n- Log: stepLogger.log('message')\n\nSYNTAX — CRITICAL:\n- WRONG: const el: Locator = page.locator(...) → RIGHT: const el = page.locator(...)\n- WRONG: import { expect } from '@playwright/test' → RIGHT: (no imports — expect is a parameter)\n- WRONG: (page: Page, baseUrl: string) → RIGHT: (page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n- Every statement must end with a semicolon or closing brace\n- Every variable declaration must use const or let\n- Verify all brackets/parens are balanced before outputting\n\nASSERTIONS — prefer resilient checks:\n- Use toContainText() over exact toHaveText() when possible\n- Use toBeTruthy() only on values you are certain exist\n- Prefer toBeVisible() for element presence checks\n- If checking a count, use toHaveCount() with the expected number, not toBeTruthy()\n\nEXAMPLE (static route):\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nexport async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger) {\n  stepLogger.log('Navigate');\n  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/settings\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });\n  await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n  await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/settings/);\n  await expect(page.locator('body')).toBeVisible();\n  stepLogger.log('Screenshot');\n  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true });\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nEXAMPLE (dynamic route — discover real ID from list page):\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nexport async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger) {\n  stepLogger.log('Navigate to list page to find a real item');\n  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/tests\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });\n  await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n  const firstLink = page.locator('a[href*=\"/tests/\"]').first();\n  await expect(firstLink).toBeVisible();\n  const href = await firstLink.getAttribute('href');\n  stepLogger.log('Navigate to detail page');\n  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}\\${href}\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });\n  await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n  await expect(page.locator('body')).toBeVisible();\n  stepLogger.log('Screenshot');\n  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true });\n}\n\\`\\`\\``;\n\nexport function createTestPrompt(context: TestGenerationContext): string {\n  const parts: string[] = [];\n\n  if (context.useMCP) {\n    parts.push('Use MCP tools to explore the page, then generate standard Playwright test code.');\n\n    if (context.userPrompt) {\n      parts.push(`\\nTest objective: ${context.userPrompt}`);\n    }\n\n    if (context.targetUrl || context.routePath) {\n      const route = context.targetUrl || context.routePath;\n      parts.push(`\\nTarget: ${route}`);\n\n      if (context.isDynamicRoute) {\n        parts.push(`\\nThis is a DYNAMIC route with parameters. You MUST:`);\n        parts.push(`1. First browser_navigate to a parent/list page`);\n        parts.push(`2. Use browser_snapshot to find links with actual IDs`);\n        parts.push(`3. Navigate to discovered URL with real parameters`);\n\n        if (context.siblingRoutes?.length) {\n          parts.push(`\\nRelated routes that may help find real data: ${context.siblingRoutes.join(', ')}`);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // Add scan context if available\n    if (context.scanContext) {\n      parts.push(buildScanContextSection(context.scanContext));\n    }\n\n    // Add codebase intelligence if available\n    if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n      parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n    }\n\n    parts.push(`\\nWorkflow: navigate → snapshot → explore → OUTPUT Playwright test code with discovered selectors`);\n    return parts.join('\\n');\n  }\n\n  parts.push('Generate a Playwright visual regression test.');\n\n  if (context.userPrompt) {\n    parts.push(`\\nTest objective: ${context.userPrompt}`);\n  }\n\n  if (context.targetUrl || context.routePath) {\n    const route = context.targetUrl || context.routePath;\n    parts.push(`\\nTarget: ${route}`);\n\n    if (context.isDynamicRoute) {\n      parts.push(`\\nIMPORTANT: This is a dynamic route. Before testing it directly:`);\n      parts.push(`1. Navigate to the parent list page first (e.g., for /users/[id], go to /users)`);\n      parts.push(`2. Wait for the list to load and find a valid link`);\n      parts.push(`3. Click the link or extract the href to get a real ID`);\n      parts.push(`4. Then test the actual page with real data`);\n\n      if (context.siblingRoutes?.length) {\n        parts.push(`\\nRelated routes: ${context.siblingRoutes.join(', ')}`);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Add scan context if available\n  if (context.scanContext) {\n    parts.push(buildScanContextSection(context.scanContext));\n  }\n\n  // Add codebase intelligence if available\n  if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n    parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n  }\n\n  if (context.availableRoutes?.length) {\n    parts.push(`\\n--- Available Routes (ONLY navigate to these) ---`);\n    parts.push(context.availableRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n'));\n    parts.push(`\\nCRITICAL: Do NOT invent or guess URLs. ONLY use routes from the list above.`);\n    parts.push(`If the test objective refers to a page not in this list, navigate to the closest matching route.`);\n  }\n\n  // Add guidelines and requirements sections\n  parts.push(`\n--- Requirements ---\n- Plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n- Signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n- URL checks: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n- Content checks: await expect(page.locator('body')).toBeVisible()\n- Screenshot: await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true })\n- Log actions: stepLogger.log('message')\n\nReturn ONLY the code block, no explanations.`);\n\n  return parts.join('\\n');\n}\n\nfunction buildScanContextSection(scanContext: import('./types').ScanContext): string {\n  const lines: string[] = ['\\n--- Discovery Context ---'];\n\n  // Add source-specific context\n  if (scanContext.discoverySource === 'nav-link' && scanContext.navLabel) {\n    lines.push(`This route appears in navigation as \"${scanContext.navLabel}\".`);\n    lines.push('Verify the page matches its navigation label purpose.');\n  }\n\n  if (scanContext.discoverySource === 'spec-analysis' && scanContext.specDescription) {\n    lines.push(`From specification: ${scanContext.specDescription}`);\n    lines.push('Test the documented behavior.');\n  }\n\n  if (scanContext.discoverySource === 'file-scan' && scanContext.sourceFilePath) {\n    lines.push(`Source file: ${scanContext.sourceFilePath}`);\n  }\n\n  // Add framework hint\n  if (scanContext.framework) {\n    lines.push(`Framework: ${scanContext.framework}`);\n  }\n\n  // Add router type if relevant\n  if (scanContext.routerType) {\n    lines.push(`Router: ${scanContext.routerType}`);\n  }\n\n  // Add test suggestions as scenarios to consider\n  if (scanContext.testSuggestions && scanContext.testSuggestions.length > 0) {\n    lines.push('\\nSuggested scenarios to consider:');\n    for (const suggestion of scanContext.testSuggestions) {\n      lines.push(`- ${suggestion}`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Add functional area context\n  if (scanContext.functionalAreaName) {\n    lines.push(`\\nFunctional area: ${scanContext.functionalAreaName}`);\n    if (scanContext.functionalAreaDescription) {\n      lines.push(`Context: ${scanContext.functionalAreaDescription}`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return lines.join('\\n');\n}\n\nfunction buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(intel: CodebaseIntelligenceContext): string {\n  const lines: string[] = ['\\n--- Project Intelligence ---'];\n\n  if (intel.framework) lines.push(`Framework: ${intel.framework}`);\n  if (intel.cssFramework) lines.push(`CSS: ${intel.cssFramework}`);\n  if (intel.selectorStrategy) lines.push(`Selector strategy: ${intel.selectorStrategy}`);\n  if (intel.authMechanism && intel.authMechanism !== 'none detected') {\n    lines.push(`Auth: ${intel.authMechanism} — protected routes may redirect to login`);\n  }\n  if (intel.stateManagement) lines.push(`State management: ${intel.stateManagement}`);\n  if (intel.apiLayer) lines.push(`API layer: ${intel.apiLayer}`);\n  if (intel.projectDescription) lines.push(`App: ${intel.projectDescription}`);\n\n  if (intel.testingRecommendations && intel.testingRecommendations.length > 0) {\n    lines.push('\\nTesting recommendations:');\n    for (const rec of intel.testingRecommendations.slice(0, 8)) {\n      lines.push(`- ${rec}`);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return lines.join('\\n');\n}\n\nexport function createFixPrompt(context: TestGenerationContext): string {\n  const parts: string[] = [`Fix this failing Playwright test.\n\nOriginal test code:\n\\`\\`\\`typescript\n${context.existingCode}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nError message:\n${context.errorMessage}`];\n\n  if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n    parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n  }\n\n  if (context.availableRoutes?.length) {\n    parts.push(`\\nAvailable Routes (ONLY use these in page.goto()):`);\n    parts.push(context.availableRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n'));\n    parts.push(`If the current page.goto() URL is not in this list, change it to the closest matching route.`);\n  }\n\n  parts.push(`\nERROR DIAGNOSIS — identify the category FIRST, then apply the matching fix strategy:\n- \"Unexpected identifier\" or \"Unexpected token\" → SYNTAX ERROR: Look for missing commas, semicolons, or unmatched brackets. Remove any TypeScript annotations (: Type, as Type). Remove any import statements.\n- \"404\" or \"not found\" → WRONG URL: The page.goto() URL doesn't exist. Change it to a route from the available routes list.\n- \"timeout\" or \"waiting for selector\" → SELECTOR MISMATCH: The element doesn't exist with that selector. Use broader selectors (getByRole, getByText) or remove the assertion.\n- \"X is not a function\" → INVALID API: Using a non-existent method. Check expect() matcher names and Playwright API.\n- \"Expected\" + \"Received\" → ASSERTION FAILURE: The page content doesn't match expectations. Loosen the assertion or use a more flexible match (toContain instead of toBe, regex instead of exact string).\n- \"login\" or \"redirect\" or \"sign-in\" → AUTH ISSUE: Add auth state check — if (page.url().includes('/login')) return;\n- \"net::ERR\" or \"ERR_CONNECTION\" → NETWORK ERROR: The server may not be ready. Add waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded').\n\nInstructions:\n1. Identify which error category above matches the error message\n2. Apply ONLY the minimal fix for that category — do not rewrite the entire test\n3. Verify your fix actually changes something (not identical to input)\n\nRules:\n- Write plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript type annotations (no \": Page\", no \": string\", no \": any\")\n- Do NOT use \\`import\\` — expect is provided by the runner\n- ALWAYS use regex for URL checks: await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/); — never exact string URLs\n- Never mix regex text and CSS selectors in one locator — use page.getByText(/pattern/i) for regex\n\nReturn ONLY the fixed code, no explanations.`);\n\n  return parts.join('\\n');\n}\n\nexport function createMcpFixPrompt(context: TestGenerationContext): string {\n  return `Fix this failing Playwright test by exploring the live page with MCP tools.\n\nOriginal test code:\n\\`\\`\\`typescript\n${context.existingCode}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nError message:\n${context.errorMessage}\n\nTarget URL: ${context.targetUrl || 'unknown'}\n\nInstructions:\n- browser_navigate to the target URL, then browser_snapshot to see current page structure\n- Compare actual page selectors/content with the failing test to identify what changed\n- Fix the test using discovered selectors; maintain the same function signature and intent\n- Write plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript type annotations, NO imports\n- ALWAYS use regex for URL checks: await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/);\n- Use only valid matchers (toBe, toEqual, toBeTruthy, toBeFalsy, toContain, toMatch, toHaveURL, toHaveTitle, toBeVisible, toHaveText, toContainText, toHaveAttribute, toHaveCount, etc.)\n- Never mix regex text and CSS selectors in one locator — use page.getByText(/pattern/i) for regex\n\nReturn ONLY the fixed code, no explanations.`;\n}\n\nexport function createEnhancePrompt(context: TestGenerationContext): string {\n  const parts: string[] = [];\n\n  parts.push(`Enhance this Playwright visual regression test:\n\nCurrent test code:\n\\`\\`\\`typescript\n${context.existingCode}\n\\`\\`\\``);\n\n  if (context.userPrompt) {\n    parts.push(`\\nEnhancement request: ${context.userPrompt}`);\n  } else {\n    parts.push(`\\nEnhancements to make:\n- Add more assertions to verify page state\n- Improve selector reliability\n- Add checks for common edge cases\n- Improve logging with stepLogger\n- Add waits for dynamic content`);\n  }\n\n  parts.push(`\\nReturn ONLY the enhanced code, no explanations.`);\n\n  return parts.join('\\n');\n}\n\nexport function createRouteScanPrompt(codebaseContext: string, repoFullName?: string, intelligence?: CodebaseIntelligenceContext): string {\n  const repoLine = repoFullName ? `\\nRepository: ${repoFullName}\\n` : '';\n  const intelSection = intelligence ? buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(intelligence) : '';\n  return `Analyze this codebase structure and identify all testable routes/pages.\n${repoLine}${intelSection}\nCodebase context:\n${codebaseContext}\n\nReturn a JSON object with a flat array of routes:\n{\n  \"routes\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"/users\",\n      \"type\": \"static\",\n      \"functionalArea\": \"User Management\",\n      \"description\": \"User listing page\",\n      \"testSuggestions\": [\"Verify user list loads\", \"Check pagination\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"/users/[id]\",\n      \"type\": \"dynamic\",\n      \"functionalArea\": \"User Management\",\n      \"description\": \"User profile page\",\n      \"testSuggestions\": [\"Test with valid user ID\", \"Test error state for invalid ID\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"/dashboard\",\n      \"type\": \"static\",\n      \"functionalArea\": \"Dashboard\",\n      \"description\": \"Main dashboard page\",\n      \"testSuggestions\": [\"Verify dashboard loads\", \"Check metric widgets\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nGuidelines:\n- Include all user-facing pages that benefit from visual regression testing\n- Mark routes as \"static\" or \"dynamic\" based on URL parameters\n- Use \"functionalArea\" to label the logical group (e.g. \"Authentication\", \"Settings\")\n- Provide brief test suggestions for each route\n\nReturn ONLY the JSON object, no explanations.`;\n}\n\nexport function createCodeDiffScanPrompt(\n  changedFilesContext: string,\n  baseBranch: string,\n  headBranch: string,\n  repoFullName?: string\n): string {\n  const repoNote = repoFullName ? `\\nRepository: ${repoFullName}` : '';\n  return `You are analyzing code changes between two git branches to identify what visual regression tests should be created to cover the specific changes.\n${repoNote}\nBase branch: ${baseBranch}\nHead branch: ${headBranch}\n\nChanged files and their contents:\n${changedFilesContext}\n\nAnalyze the actual code changes above and identify:\n1. What specific functionality was added or modified\n2. Which user-facing pages/routes are affected by these changes\n3. What specific behaviors should be tested based on the diff\n\nFor each affected route, generate test suggestions that target the EXACT changes — not generic page checks. For example:\n- If a new button was added → \"Test the new [button name] button click behavior\"\n- If form validation changed → \"Verify updated validation rules for [field]\"\n- If a component was restyled → \"Check visual appearance of [component] after style changes\"\n- If a new page was added → \"Test the new [page] route renders correctly with expected elements\"\n\nReturn a JSON object with this exact structure:\n{\n  \"functionalAreas\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Area Name\",\n      \"description\": \"Brief description of what changed in this area\",\n      \"routes\": [\n        {\n          \"path\": \"/affected-route\",\n          \"type\": \"static\",\n          \"description\": \"What changed on this page\",\n          \"testSuggestions\": [\"Specific test targeting the actual code change\"]\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nGuidelines:\n- Group changes under logical functional areas based on what was modified\n- Only include routes that are actually affected by the code changes\n- Test suggestions MUST reference the specific change, not generic \"verify page loads\"\n- Mark routes as \"static\" or \"dynamic\" based on URL parameters\n- For dynamic routes, use bracket notation: /users/[id]\n- If changes are purely backend/non-visual, still suggest routes where the effects would be visible\n\nReturn ONLY the JSON object, no explanations or markdown formatting.`;\n}\n\nexport function createSpecAnalysisPrompt(specContent: string): string {\n  return `Analyze the following specification/documentation content and extract functional areas, routes, and test scenarios.\n\nSpecification content:\n${specContent}\n\nReturn a JSON object with this exact structure:\n{\n  \"functionalAreas\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"Area Name\",\n      \"description\": \"Brief description of this functional area\",\n      \"routes\": [\n        {\n          \"path\": \"/example-path\",\n          \"type\": \"static\",\n          \"description\": \"What this route does\"\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"testScenarios\": [\n    {\n      \"route\": \"/example-path\",\n      \"suggestions\": [\"Test scenario 1\", \"Test scenario 2\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\nGuidelines:\n- Group related routes under logical functional areas\n- Route type should be \"static\" or \"dynamic\" (dynamic routes have parameters like [id])\n- For dynamic routes, use bracket notation: /users/[id]\n- Test scenarios should be actionable visual regression test descriptions\n- Focus on user-facing pages that benefit from visual testing\n- Extract as many meaningful routes and test scenarios as possible from the spec\n\nReturn ONLY the JSON object, no explanations or markdown formatting.`;\n}\n\nexport function createMCPExploreRoutesPrompt(baseURL: string, existingRoutes: string[], intelligence?: CodebaseIntelligenceContext): string {\n  const seedSection = existingRoutes.length > 0\n    ? `\\nAlready known routes (use as seed starting points to explore deeper):\\n${existingRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n')}`\n    : '';\n  const intelSection = intelligence ? buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(intelligence) : '';\n\n  return `You are exploring a live web application to discover all available routes/pages.\n\nBase URL: ${baseURL}\n${seedSection}${intelSection}\n\nEXPLORATION INSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Navigate to ${baseURL} and snapshot to find navigation links, sidebars, menus\n2. Click through discovered links and record each unique URL pathname\n3. Look for sub-navigation, tabs, or nested links on each page\n4. Visit any known routes listed above as additional starting points\n5. Note whether each route is static or dynamic (has IDs/slugs in the URL)\n\nIMPORTANT:\n- Only record routes belonging to this application (same origin as baseURL)\n- Convert dynamic segments to bracket notation (e.g., /users/123 → /users/[id])\n- Do NOT include hash fragments, query parameters, or external links\n\nReturn a flat JSON array of discovered routes:\n\\`\\`\\`json\n{\n  \"routes\": [\n    {\"path\": \"/dashboard\", \"type\": \"static\", \"functionalArea\": \"Dashboard\", \"description\": \"Main dashboard page\", \"testSuggestions\": [\"Verify dashboard loads correctly\", \"Check navigation elements\"]},\n    {\"path\": \"/users/[id]\", \"type\": \"dynamic\", \"functionalArea\": \"User Management\", \"description\": \"User profile page\", \"testSuggestions\": [\"Test with valid user ID\", \"Test error state for invalid ID\"]}\n  ]\n}\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nUse \"functionalArea\" to label the logical group for each route (e.g. \"Authentication\", \"Settings\").\n\nReturn ONLY the JSON object inside a code block, no other text.`;\n}\n\nexport function createUserStoryExtractionPrompt(specContent: string): string {\n  return `Analyze the following specification/requirements document and extract all User Stories (US) and their Acceptance Criteria (AC).\n\nDocument content:\n${specContent}\n\nExtract User Stories and Acceptance Criteria with the following rules:\n1. Each distinct feature or capability should be its own User Story\n2. Each User Story should have clear, testable Acceptance Criteria\n3. Group related ACs under the same User Story\n4. Provide a descriptive name for each AC that works as a test name\n\nFormat your response as markdown using this exact structure:\n\n### User Story 1: [Functional area name]\n**As a** [role]\n**I want to** [feature/capability]\n**So that** [benefit/value]\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- AC1: [Clear, testable criterion that describes expected behavior]\n- AC2: [Another criterion]\n\n### User Story 2: [Next functional area]\n...\n\nGuidelines:\n- User Story titles should be concise functional area names (e.g., \"User Authentication\", \"Dashboard Analytics\")\n- Each AC MUST describe a specific, observable user action and expected system response that can be verified in a browser\n- DO NOT include: questions, suggestions, meta-commentary, implementation tasks, or vague criteria\n- DO NOT include ACs like \"Create additional tests...\", \"Consider...\", \"Should we...\", \"Implement...\", \"Ensure proper...\"\n- Bad AC: \"Ensure proper error handling\" (vague, not testable)\n- Good AC: \"When user submits login form with wrong password, an error message 'Invalid credentials' appears\"\n- Each AC should be independently testable in a browser-based visual regression test\n- If a requirement is not testable via browser interaction, skip it\n- If the document doesn't follow formal US/AC format, infer them from the requirements`;\n}\n\nexport function createBranchAwareTestPrompt(context: {\n  testName: string;\n  acceptanceCriteria: string;\n  userStoryTitle: string;\n  userStoryDescription: string;\n  targetUrl?: string;\n  branchChanges?: {\n    changedFiles: string[];\n    fileDiffs?: string;\n  };\n  codebaseIntelligence?: CodebaseIntelligenceContext;\n  availableRoutes?: string[];\n}): string {\n  const parts: string[] = [];\n\n  parts.push(`Generate a Playwright visual regression test for the following acceptance criterion.\n\nUser Story: ${context.userStoryTitle}\n${context.userStoryDescription}\n\nAcceptance Criterion: ${context.acceptanceCriteria}\nTest Name: ${context.testName}`);\n\n  if (context.targetUrl) {\n    parts.push(`\\nTarget URL: ${context.targetUrl}`);\n  }\n\n  if (context.branchChanges) {\n    parts.push(`\\n--- Branch Code Context ---`);\n    parts.push(`The following files have been changed in the branch:`);\n    for (const file of context.branchChanges.changedFiles) {\n      parts.push(`- ${file}`);\n    }\n    if (context.branchChanges.fileDiffs) {\n      parts.push(`\\nRelevant code changes:\\n${context.branchChanges.fileDiffs}`);\n    }\n    parts.push(`\\nUse this context to write more accurate selectors and assertions based on the actual code changes.`);\n  }\n\n  if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n    parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n  }\n\n  if (context.availableRoutes?.length) {\n    parts.push(`\\n--- Available Routes (ONLY navigate to these) ---`);\n    parts.push(context.availableRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n'));\n    parts.push(`\\nCRITICAL: Do NOT invent or guess URLs. ONLY use routes from the list above.`);\n    parts.push(`If the acceptance criterion refers to a page not in this list, navigate to the closest matching route and test what is available there.`);\n  }\n\n  parts.push(`\n--- Guidelines ---\n- Write the test to verify the acceptance criterion\n- Use descriptive stepLogger.log() messages matching the AC steps\n- Add assertions that verify the expected behavior\n- Capture screenshots at meaningful states\n- Handle loading states for stable screenshots\n\nDYNAMIC ROUTES (paths with [id], [slug], etc.):\n- First navigate to the parent list page (e.g., for /tests/[id], go to /tests)\n- Wait for the page to load, then find a link or row in the list\n- Click the first item or extract its href to get a real URL with an actual ID\n- Then test the detail page with real data\n- NEVER hardcode fake IDs like \"123\" or \"test-id\"\n\nSELECTORS (this app uses shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS):\n- Buttons: page.getByRole('button', { name: '...' })\n- Inputs: page.getByRole('textbox') or page.getByLabel('...')\n- Tabs: page.getByRole('tab', { name: '...' })\n- Dialog: page.getByRole('dialog')\n- Links: page.getByRole('link', { name: '...' })\n- Headings: page.getByRole('heading', { name: '...' })\n- Prefer getByRole/getByText/getByLabel over CSS selectors\n\nLOADING STATES:\n- After navigation: await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n- Before assertions: allow time for dynamic content to render\n- For async data: await page.locator('[data-loading]').waitFor({ state: 'hidden', timeout: 5000 }).catch(() => {})\n\n--- Requirements ---\n- Plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n- Function signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n- URL checks: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n- At least one screenshot must be captured\n- Use baseUrl parameter for navigation\n- ASSERTIONS: prefer toBeVisible() for element checks, toContainText() for text, regex toHaveURL() for URLs\n- NEVER use toBeTruthy() on a value that might not exist — use toBeVisible() on the locator instead\n\nReturn ONLY the code block, no explanations.`);\n\n  return parts.join('\\n');\n}\n\nexport function extractCodeFromResponse(response: string): string {\n  // Try to extract code from markdown code blocks\n  const codeBlockMatch = response.match(/```(?:typescript|ts|javascript|js)?\\n([\\s\\S]*?)```/);\n  if (codeBlockMatch) {\n    return codeBlockMatch[1].trim();\n  }\n\n  // If no code block, check if response starts with import or export\n  if (response.trim().startsWith('import') || response.trim().startsWith('export')) {\n    return response.trim();\n  }\n\n  // Return as-is if we can't extract\n  return response.trim();\n}\n","numLines":686,"startLine":1,"totalLines":686}}}
