{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GnqMPN6QgTR2DeNKPHgfat","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Track B: Test Generation Quality\n     2→\n     3→## Goal\n     4→Improve the quality of generated tests: valid syntax, proper structure, no antipatterns.\n     5→\n     6→## Current Problem\n     7→Tests sometimes contain TypeScript annotations, import statements, or invalid syntax that causes runtime failures.\n     8→\n     9→## Scope — What You Can Modify\n    10→- `SYSTEM_PROMPT` in `src/lib/ai/prompts.ts`\n    11→- Requirements section of `createTestPrompt()` and `createBranchAwareTestPrompt()`\n    12→- `createUserStoryExtractionPrompt()` — AC grouping guidance\n    13→\n    14→## Experiments\n    15→\n    16→### B1: Stronger no-TypeScript enforcement\n    17→Add explicit examples of what NOT to do:\n    18→```\n    19→WRONG: const element: Locator = page.locator(...)\n    20→RIGHT: const element = page.locator(...)\n    21→WRONG: import { expect } from '@playwright/test'\n    22→RIGHT: (no imports — expect is provided as a parameter)\n    23→```\n    24→\n    25→### B2: Multi-route test guidance\n    26→Instruct AI to cover 2-3 related ACs in one test when they share a route:\n    27→```\n    28→If multiple acceptance criteria target the same route, combine them into ONE test that:\n    29→1. Navigates to the route once\n    30→2. Verifies each criterion sequentially\n    31→3. Takes screenshots at key verification points\n    32→```\n    33→\n    34→### B3: Route-aware test naming\n    35→Include target route in test name for traceability:\n    36→```\n    37→Name your test: \"[route] - [what it tests]\"\n    38→Example: \"/settings - verify theme toggle works\"\n    39→```\n    40→\n    41→### B4: Loading state handling\n    42→Add explicit guidance for common loading patterns:\n    43→```\n    44→After navigation, ALWAYS:\n    45→1. await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n    46→2. Wait for any loading indicators to disappear: await page.locator('[data-loading]').waitFor({ state: 'hidden', timeout: 5000 }).catch(() => {})\n    47→```\n    48→\n    49→### B5: shadcn/ui selector patterns\n    50→Add selector guidance specific to the UI framework:\n    51→```\n    52→This app uses shadcn/ui. Prefer these selectors:\n    53→- Buttons: page.getByRole('button', { name: '...' })\n    54→- Inputs: page.getByRole('textbox') or page.getByLabel('...')\n    55→- Tabs: page.getByRole('tab', { name: '...' })\n    56→- Dialog: page.getByRole('dialog')\n    57→```\n    58→\n    59→### B6: AC grouping in extraction prompt\n    60→Improve `createUserStoryExtractionPrompt` to group related ACs:\n    61→```\n    62→Group acceptance criteria that:\n    63→- Target the same page/route\n    64→- Test related functionality (e.g., form fields on the same form)\n    65→- Share setup steps (e.g., both need to navigate to settings)\n    66→Set groupedWith to the first AC's ID in the group.\n    67→```\n    68→\n    69→### B7: Concrete example test\n    70→Add a full working example test in SYSTEM_PROMPT that demonstrates all best practices.\n    71→\n    72→## Metric\n    73→- Primary: `syntax_quality` from metrics.ts (target = 1.0)\n    74→- Secondary: `pass_rate` improvement from better test structure\n    75→- Fast eval: `evalTestGeneration` — generates tests, syntax-checks, checks for antipatterns\n    76→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"d016bcca-3325-41fe-a9c3-499020359c00","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ewyct/dev/lastest2/autoresearch/tracks/test-generation.md","content":"# Track B: Test Generation Quality\n\n## Goal\nImprove the quality of generated tests: valid syntax, proper structure, no antipatterns.\n\n## Current Problem\nTests sometimes contain TypeScript annotations, import statements, or invalid syntax that causes runtime failures.\n\n## Scope — What You Can Modify\n- `SYSTEM_PROMPT` in `src/lib/ai/prompts.ts`\n- Requirements section of `createTestPrompt()` and `createBranchAwareTestPrompt()`\n- `createUserStoryExtractionPrompt()` — AC grouping guidance\n\n## Experiments\n\n### B1: Stronger no-TypeScript enforcement\nAdd explicit examples of what NOT to do:\n```\nWRONG: const element: Locator = page.locator(...)\nRIGHT: const element = page.locator(...)\nWRONG: import { expect } from '@playwright/test'\nRIGHT: (no imports — expect is provided as a parameter)\n```\n\n### B2: Multi-route test guidance\nInstruct AI to cover 2-3 related ACs in one test when they share a route:\n```\nIf multiple acceptance criteria target the same route, combine them into ONE test that:\n1. Navigates to the route once\n2. Verifies each criterion sequentially\n3. Takes screenshots at key verification points\n```\n\n### B3: Route-aware test naming\nInclude target route in test name for traceability:\n```\nName your test: \"[route] - [what it tests]\"\nExample: \"/settings - verify theme toggle works\"\n```\n\n### B4: Loading state handling\nAdd explicit guidance for common loading patterns:\n```\nAfter navigation, ALWAYS:\n1. await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n2. Wait for any loading indicators to disappear: await page.locator('[data-loading]').waitFor({ state: 'hidden', timeout: 5000 }).catch(() => {})\n```\n\n### B5: shadcn/ui selector patterns\nAdd selector guidance specific to the UI framework:\n```\nThis app uses shadcn/ui. Prefer these selectors:\n- Buttons: page.getByRole('button', { name: '...' })\n- Inputs: page.getByRole('textbox') or page.getByLabel('...')\n- Tabs: page.getByRole('tab', { name: '...' })\n- Dialog: page.getByRole('dialog')\n```\n\n### B6: AC grouping in extraction prompt\nImprove `createUserStoryExtractionPrompt` to group related ACs:\n```\nGroup acceptance criteria that:\n- Target the same page/route\n- Test related functionality (e.g., form fields on the same form)\n- Share setup steps (e.g., both need to navigate to settings)\nSet groupedWith to the first AC's ID in the group.\n```\n\n### B7: Concrete example test\nAdd a full working example test in SYSTEM_PROMPT that demonstrates all best practices.\n\n## Metric\n- Primary: `syntax_quality` from metrics.ts (target = 1.0)\n- Secondary: `pass_rate` improvement from better test structure\n- Fast eval: `evalTestGeneration` — generates tests, syntax-checks, checks for antipatterns\n","numLines":76,"startLine":1,"totalLines":76}}}
