{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DUyoQ6vGLUWpeTDqj7dWGH","type":"tool_result","content":"   640→    parts.push(`\\n--- Branch Code Context ---`);\n   641→    parts.push(`The following files have been changed in the branch:`);\n   642→    for (const file of context.branchChanges.changedFiles) {\n   643→      parts.push(`- ${file}`);\n   644→    }\n   645→    if (context.branchChanges.fileDiffs) {\n   646→      parts.push(`\\nRelevant code changes:\\n${context.branchChanges.fileDiffs}`);\n   647→    }\n   648→    parts.push(`\\nUse this context to write more accurate selectors and assertions based on the actual code changes.`);\n   649→  }\n   650→\n   651→  if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n   652→    parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n   653→  }\n   654→\n   655→  if (context.availableRoutes?.length) {\n   656→    parts.push(`\\n--- Available Routes (ONLY navigate to these) ---`);\n   657→    parts.push(context.availableRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n'));\n   658→    parts.push(`\\nCRITICAL: Do NOT invent or guess URLs. ONLY use routes from the list above.`);\n   659→    parts.push(`If the acceptance criterion refers to a page not in this list, navigate to the closest matching route and test what is available there.`);\n   660→  }\n   661→\n   662→  parts.push(`\n   663→--- Guidelines ---\n   664→- Write the test to verify the acceptance criterion\n   665→- Use descriptive stepLogger.log() messages matching the AC steps\n   666→- Add assertions that verify the expected behavior\n   667→- Capture screenshots at meaningful states\n   668→- Handle loading states for stable screenshots\n   669→\n   670→DYNAMIC ROUTES (paths with [id], [slug], etc.):\n   671→- First navigate to the parent list page (e.g., for /tests/[id], go to /tests)\n   672→- Wait for the page to load, then find a link or row in the list\n   673→- Click the first item or extract its href to get a real URL with an actual ID\n   674→- Then test the detail page with real data\n   675→- NEVER hardcode fake IDs like \"123\" or \"test-id\"\n   676→\n   677→SELECTORS (this app uses shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS):\n   678→- Buttons: page.getByRole('button', { name: '...' })\n   679→- Inputs: page.getByRole('textbox') or page.getByLabel('...')\n   680→- Tabs: page.getByRole('tab', { name: '...' })\n   681→- Dialog: page.getByRole('dialog')\n   682→- Links: page.getByRole('link', { name: '...' })\n   683→- Headings: page.getByRole('heading', { name: '...' })\n   684→- Prefer getByRole/getByText/getByLabel over CSS selectors\n   685→\n   686→LOADING STATES:\n   687→- After navigation: await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n   688→- Before assertions: allow time for dynamic content to render\n   689→- For async data: await page.locator('[data-loading]').waitFor({ state: 'hidden', timeout: 5000 }).catch(() => {})\n   690→\n   691→--- Requirements ---\n   692→- Plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n   693→- Function signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n   694→- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n   695→- URL checks: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n   696→- At least one screenshot must be captured\n   697→- Use baseUrl parameter for navigation\n   698→- ASSERTIONS: prefer toBeVisible() for element checks, toContainText() for text, regex toHaveURL() for URLs\n   699→- NEVER use toBeTruthy() on a value that might not exist — use toBeVisible() on the locator instead"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"84d121b9-f6f2-4b20-9502-dfd28b245686","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ewyct/dev/lastest2/src/lib/ai/prompts.ts","content":"    parts.push(`\\n--- Branch Code Context ---`);\n    parts.push(`The following files have been changed in the branch:`);\n    for (const file of context.branchChanges.changedFiles) {\n      parts.push(`- ${file}`);\n    }\n    if (context.branchChanges.fileDiffs) {\n      parts.push(`\\nRelevant code changes:\\n${context.branchChanges.fileDiffs}`);\n    }\n    parts.push(`\\nUse this context to write more accurate selectors and assertions based on the actual code changes.`);\n  }\n\n  if (context.codebaseIntelligence) {\n    parts.push(buildCodebaseIntelligenceSection(context.codebaseIntelligence));\n  }\n\n  if (context.availableRoutes?.length) {\n    parts.push(`\\n--- Available Routes (ONLY navigate to these) ---`);\n    parts.push(context.availableRoutes.map(r => `- ${r}`).join('\\n'));\n    parts.push(`\\nCRITICAL: Do NOT invent or guess URLs. ONLY use routes from the list above.`);\n    parts.push(`If the acceptance criterion refers to a page not in this list, navigate to the closest matching route and test what is available there.`);\n  }\n\n  parts.push(`\n--- Guidelines ---\n- Write the test to verify the acceptance criterion\n- Use descriptive stepLogger.log() messages matching the AC steps\n- Add assertions that verify the expected behavior\n- Capture screenshots at meaningful states\n- Handle loading states for stable screenshots\n\nDYNAMIC ROUTES (paths with [id], [slug], etc.):\n- First navigate to the parent list page (e.g., for /tests/[id], go to /tests)\n- Wait for the page to load, then find a link or row in the list\n- Click the first item or extract its href to get a real URL with an actual ID\n- Then test the detail page with real data\n- NEVER hardcode fake IDs like \"123\" or \"test-id\"\n\nSELECTORS (this app uses shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS):\n- Buttons: page.getByRole('button', { name: '...' })\n- Inputs: page.getByRole('textbox') or page.getByLabel('...')\n- Tabs: page.getByRole('tab', { name: '...' })\n- Dialog: page.getByRole('dialog')\n- Links: page.getByRole('link', { name: '...' })\n- Headings: page.getByRole('heading', { name: '...' })\n- Prefer getByRole/getByText/getByLabel over CSS selectors\n\nLOADING STATES:\n- After navigation: await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n- Before assertions: allow time for dynamic content to render\n- For async data: await page.locator('[data-loading]').waitFor({ state: 'hidden', timeout: 5000 }).catch(() => {})\n\n--- Requirements ---\n- Plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n- Function signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n- URL checks: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n- At least one screenshot must be captured\n- Use baseUrl parameter for navigation\n- ASSERTIONS: prefer toBeVisible() for element checks, toContainText() for text, regex toHaveURL() for URLs\n- NEVER use toBeTruthy() on a value that might not exist — use toBeVisible() on the locator instead","numLines":60,"startLine":640,"totalLines":721}}}
