{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FK8i45jekse2PBuXmLKbXK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Track A: Route Accuracy\n     2→\n     3→## Goal\n     4→Ensure generated tests navigate ONLY to routes that exist in the application.\n     5→\n     6→## Current Problem\n     7→85% of Play Agent failures are 404s from hallucinated routes. The AI invents URLs that don't exist.\n     8→\n     9→## Scope — What You Can Modify\n    10→- `createBranchAwareTestPrompt()` in `src/lib/ai/prompts.ts` — specifically the `availableRoutes` constraint section\n    11→- `createTestPrompt()` — the route constraint wording\n    12→- Route presentation format in both functions\n    13→\n    14→## Experiments\n    15→\n    16→### A1: Stricter constraint phrasing\n    17→Change the available routes section to use FATAL/CRITICAL language:\n    18→```\n    19→FATAL CONSTRAINT: You MUST ONLY navigate to URLs from this exact list. Navigating to ANY other URL will crash the test and fail the entire suite:\n    20→```\n    21→\n    22→### A2: Pre-match routes to ACs\n    23→Before presenting routes, add a \"best matching route\" suggestion:\n    24→```\n    25→Based on the acceptance criteria, the most likely route is: /settings\n    26→Available routes (use ONLY these): [...]\n    27→```\n    28→\n    29→### A3: Route descriptions\n    30→Instead of bare paths, include descriptions:\n    31→```\n    32→Available routes:\n    33→- / → Dashboard home page\n    34→- /settings → Application settings\n    35→- /tests → Test list and management\n    36→```\n    37→\n    38→### A4: Group routes by functional area\n    39→Present routes organized by area to help AI pick the right one:\n    40→```\n    41→Routes by area:\n    42→  Testing: /tests, /run, /record, /review\n    43→  Configuration: /settings\n    44→  Organization: /suites, /areas\n    45→```\n    46→\n    47→### A5: Fallback instruction\n    48→Add: \"If no route exactly matches the acceptance criteria, use the closest parent route (e.g., /settings instead of /settings/notifications)\"\n    49→\n    50→### A6: Route validation reminder\n    51→Add at the END of the prompt: \"BEFORE writing page.goto(), verify the URL is in the available routes list above.\"\n    52→\n    53→### A7: Negative examples\n    54→Add: \"WRONG: page.goto(`${baseUrl}/settings/integrations`) — this route does NOT exist. RIGHT: page.goto(`${baseUrl}/settings`) — this is in the available routes list.\"\n    55→\n    56→## Metric\n    57→- Primary: `route_accuracy` from metrics.ts (target ≥ 0.95)\n    58→- Fast eval: `evalRouteAccuracy` — regenerates 404-failed tests, checks if goto URLs match routes table\n    59→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"851dfc0a-6727-4f68-86e9-404957a8efb1","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ewyct/dev/lastest2/autoresearch/tracks/route-accuracy.md","content":"# Track A: Route Accuracy\n\n## Goal\nEnsure generated tests navigate ONLY to routes that exist in the application.\n\n## Current Problem\n85% of Play Agent failures are 404s from hallucinated routes. The AI invents URLs that don't exist.\n\n## Scope — What You Can Modify\n- `createBranchAwareTestPrompt()` in `src/lib/ai/prompts.ts` — specifically the `availableRoutes` constraint section\n- `createTestPrompt()` — the route constraint wording\n- Route presentation format in both functions\n\n## Experiments\n\n### A1: Stricter constraint phrasing\nChange the available routes section to use FATAL/CRITICAL language:\n```\nFATAL CONSTRAINT: You MUST ONLY navigate to URLs from this exact list. Navigating to ANY other URL will crash the test and fail the entire suite:\n```\n\n### A2: Pre-match routes to ACs\nBefore presenting routes, add a \"best matching route\" suggestion:\n```\nBased on the acceptance criteria, the most likely route is: /settings\nAvailable routes (use ONLY these): [...]\n```\n\n### A3: Route descriptions\nInstead of bare paths, include descriptions:\n```\nAvailable routes:\n- / → Dashboard home page\n- /settings → Application settings\n- /tests → Test list and management\n```\n\n### A4: Group routes by functional area\nPresent routes organized by area to help AI pick the right one:\n```\nRoutes by area:\n  Testing: /tests, /run, /record, /review\n  Configuration: /settings\n  Organization: /suites, /areas\n```\n\n### A5: Fallback instruction\nAdd: \"If no route exactly matches the acceptance criteria, use the closest parent route (e.g., /settings instead of /settings/notifications)\"\n\n### A6: Route validation reminder\nAdd at the END of the prompt: \"BEFORE writing page.goto(), verify the URL is in the available routes list above.\"\n\n### A7: Negative examples\nAdd: \"WRONG: page.goto(`${baseUrl}/settings/integrations`) — this route does NOT exist. RIGHT: page.goto(`${baseUrl}/settings`) — this is in the available routes list.\"\n\n## Metric\n- Primary: `route_accuracy` from metrics.ts (target ≥ 0.95)\n- Fast eval: `evalRouteAccuracy` — regenerates 404-failed tests, checks if goto URLs match routes table\n","numLines":59,"startLine":1,"totalLines":59}}}
