{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015zUa2L28zaBaQmuJiz5GwU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Track C: Auth Resilience\n     2→\n     3→## Goal\n     4→Eliminate test failures caused by authentication redirects or missing auth state.\n     5→\n     6→## Current Problem\n     7→Some tests fail because they navigate to protected pages without auth, get redirected to /login, and then fail on selector assertions for the original page content.\n     8→\n     9→## Scope — What You Can Modify\n    10→- `SYSTEM_PROMPT` in `src/lib/ai/prompts.ts` — add auth awareness\n    11→- `createTestPrompt()` and `createBranchAwareTestPrompt()` — auth handling instructions\n    12→- `createFixPrompt()` — auth-aware fix strategies\n    13→\n    14→## Experiments\n    15→\n    16→### C1: Auth awareness in SYSTEM_PROMPT\n    17→Add section about auth handling:\n    18→```\n    19→AUTHENTICATION: Tests run with pre-authenticated browser state (cookies/localStorage).\n    20→If you see a login page or redirect, the test should:\n    21→1. Check if the current URL contains '/login' or '/sign-in'\n    22→2. If so, the auth state may have expired — screenshot the current state and pass\n    23→3. Do NOT try to fill in login forms — auth is handled by the test runner\n    24→```\n    25→\n    26→### C2: Login detection in generated tests\n    27→Add a helper pattern to test generation:\n    28→```\n    29→After page.goto(), check for auth redirect:\n    30→const currentUrl = page.url();\n    31→if (currentUrl.includes('/login') || currentUrl.includes('/sign-in')) {\n    32→  stepLogger.log('Auth redirect detected — skipping test');\n    33→  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath });\n    34→  return; // Pass gracefully\n    35→}\n    36→```\n    37→\n    38→### C3: Storage state awareness\n    39→Add to test generation context:\n    40→```\n    41→The test runner provides pre-authenticated browser context via Playwright storageState.\n    42→All cookies and localStorage from a prior login session are available.\n    43→If auth is required, it's already handled — don't add login steps.\n    44→```\n    45→\n    46→### C4: Auth-aware fix prompt\n    47→When a test fails with auth redirect, the fix should:\n    48→```\n    49→If error contains 'login', 'redirect', 'unauthorized', or 'sign-in':\n    50→- Do NOT add login form interactions\n    51→- Add auth state check: if (page.url().includes('/login')) return;\n    52→- Or wait longer for auth redirect to complete\n    53→```\n    54→\n    55→### C5: Pre-navigation auth check\n    56→Add pattern to test template:\n    57→```\n    58→// Navigate and handle potential auth redirect\n    59→await page.goto(`${baseUrl}/protected-route`);\n    60→await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n    61→// If redirected to login, auth expired — graceful exit\n    62→if (page.url().includes('/login')) {\n    63→  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath });\n    64→  return;\n    65→}\n    66→```\n    67→\n    68→## Metric\n    69→- Primary: `auth_success` from metrics.ts (target = 1.0)\n    70→- Fast eval: `evalAuthResilience` — checks last build for auth-redirect failures\n    71→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"385451cf-0ace-43ed-b715-dc0067e4246c","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ewyct/dev/lastest2/autoresearch/tracks/auth-resilience.md","content":"# Track C: Auth Resilience\n\n## Goal\nEliminate test failures caused by authentication redirects or missing auth state.\n\n## Current Problem\nSome tests fail because they navigate to protected pages without auth, get redirected to /login, and then fail on selector assertions for the original page content.\n\n## Scope — What You Can Modify\n- `SYSTEM_PROMPT` in `src/lib/ai/prompts.ts` — add auth awareness\n- `createTestPrompt()` and `createBranchAwareTestPrompt()` — auth handling instructions\n- `createFixPrompt()` — auth-aware fix strategies\n\n## Experiments\n\n### C1: Auth awareness in SYSTEM_PROMPT\nAdd section about auth handling:\n```\nAUTHENTICATION: Tests run with pre-authenticated browser state (cookies/localStorage).\nIf you see a login page or redirect, the test should:\n1. Check if the current URL contains '/login' or '/sign-in'\n2. If so, the auth state may have expired — screenshot the current state and pass\n3. Do NOT try to fill in login forms — auth is handled by the test runner\n```\n\n### C2: Login detection in generated tests\nAdd a helper pattern to test generation:\n```\nAfter page.goto(), check for auth redirect:\nconst currentUrl = page.url();\nif (currentUrl.includes('/login') || currentUrl.includes('/sign-in')) {\n  stepLogger.log('Auth redirect detected — skipping test');\n  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath });\n  return; // Pass gracefully\n}\n```\n\n### C3: Storage state awareness\nAdd to test generation context:\n```\nThe test runner provides pre-authenticated browser context via Playwright storageState.\nAll cookies and localStorage from a prior login session are available.\nIf auth is required, it's already handled — don't add login steps.\n```\n\n### C4: Auth-aware fix prompt\nWhen a test fails with auth redirect, the fix should:\n```\nIf error contains 'login', 'redirect', 'unauthorized', or 'sign-in':\n- Do NOT add login form interactions\n- Add auth state check: if (page.url().includes('/login')) return;\n- Or wait longer for auth redirect to complete\n```\n\n### C5: Pre-navigation auth check\nAdd pattern to test template:\n```\n// Navigate and handle potential auth redirect\nawait page.goto(`${baseUrl}/protected-route`);\nawait page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n// If redirected to login, auth expired — graceful exit\nif (page.url().includes('/login')) {\n  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath });\n  return;\n}\n```\n\n## Metric\n- Primary: `auth_success` from metrics.ts (target = 1.0)\n- Fast eval: `evalAuthResilience` — checks last build for auth-redirect failures\n","numLines":71,"startLine":1,"totalLines":71}}}
