{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0163uqyktqUS4YykrUc8ydTU","type":"tool_result","content":"   720→- Capture screenshots at meaningful states\n   721→- Handle loading states for stable screenshots\n   722→\n   723→DYNAMIC ROUTES (paths with [id], [slug], etc.):\n   724→- First navigate to the parent list page (e.g., for /tests/[id], go to /tests)\n   725→- Wait for the page to load, then find a link or row in the list\n   726→- Click the first item or extract its href to get a real URL with an actual ID\n   727→- Then test the detail page with real data\n   728→- NEVER hardcode fake IDs like \"123\" or \"test-id\"\n   729→- If no items exist in the list, take a screenshot of the empty state and return gracefully\n   730→\n   731→SELECTORS (this app uses shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS):\n   732→- Buttons: page.getByRole('button', { name: '...' })\n   733→- Inputs: page.getByRole('textbox') or page.getByLabel('...')\n   734→- Tabs: page.getByRole('tab', { name: '...' })\n   735→- Dialog: page.getByRole('dialog')\n   736→- Links: page.getByRole('link', { name: '...' })\n   737→- Headings: page.getByRole('heading', { name: '...' })\n   738→- Prefer getByRole/getByText/getByLabel over CSS selectors\n   739→\n   740→LOADING STATES:\n   741→- After navigation: await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n   742→- Before assertions: allow time for dynamic content to render\n   743→- For async data: await page.locator('[data-loading]').waitFor({ state: 'hidden', timeout: 5000 }).catch(() => {})\n   744→\n   745→--- Requirements ---\n   746→- Plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n   747→- Function signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n   748→- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n   749→- URL checks: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n   750→- At least one screenshot must be captured\n   751→- Use baseUrl parameter for navigation\n   752→- Every variable MUST be declared with const or let\n   753→- Every statement must end with a semicolon or closing brace\n   754→\n   755→ASSERTIONS — CRITICAL:\n   756→- Prefer toBeVisible() for element checks, toContainText() for text, regex toHaveURL() for URLs\n   757→- NEVER use toBeTruthy() on textContent()/getAttribute()/innerText() — they return null when element is missing\n   758→- WRONG: const text = await el.textContent(); expect(text).toBeTruthy()\n   759→- RIGHT: await expect(el).toBeVisible() or await expect(el).toContainText(/expected/)\n   760→- Available expect matchers: toBe, toEqual, toBeTruthy, toBeFalsy, toContain, toMatch, toHaveURL, toHaveTitle, toBeVisible, toBeHidden, toHaveText, toContainText, toHaveAttribute, toHaveCount, toBeEnabled, toBeDisabled, toBeChecked, toHaveValue (all support .not)\n   761→\n   762→BEFORE writing page.goto(), verify the URL is in the available routes list above. If no route matches, use the closest parent route.\n   763→\n   764→Return ONLY the code block, no explanations.`);\n   765→\n   766→  return parts.join('\\n');\n   767→}\n   768→\n   769→export function extractCodeFromResponse(response: string): string {"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"8b57e5f9-3ff6-4d7e-b611-5d65923205e1","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ewyct/dev/lastest2/src/lib/ai/prompts.ts","content":"- Capture screenshots at meaningful states\n- Handle loading states for stable screenshots\n\nDYNAMIC ROUTES (paths with [id], [slug], etc.):\n- First navigate to the parent list page (e.g., for /tests/[id], go to /tests)\n- Wait for the page to load, then find a link or row in the list\n- Click the first item or extract its href to get a real URL with an actual ID\n- Then test the detail page with real data\n- NEVER hardcode fake IDs like \"123\" or \"test-id\"\n- If no items exist in the list, take a screenshot of the empty state and return gracefully\n\nSELECTORS (this app uses shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS):\n- Buttons: page.getByRole('button', { name: '...' })\n- Inputs: page.getByRole('textbox') or page.getByLabel('...')\n- Tabs: page.getByRole('tab', { name: '...' })\n- Dialog: page.getByRole('dialog')\n- Links: page.getByRole('link', { name: '...' })\n- Headings: page.getByRole('heading', { name: '...' })\n- Prefer getByRole/getByText/getByLabel over CSS selectors\n\nLOADING STATES:\n- After navigation: await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded')\n- Before assertions: allow time for dynamic content to render\n- For async data: await page.locator('[data-loading]').waitFor({ state: 'hidden', timeout: 5000 }).catch(() => {})\n\n--- Requirements ---\n- Plain JavaScript only — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n- Function signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n- Navigate: await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' })\n- URL checks: ALWAYS regex — await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n- At least one screenshot must be captured\n- Use baseUrl parameter for navigation\n- Every variable MUST be declared with const or let\n- Every statement must end with a semicolon or closing brace\n\nASSERTIONS — CRITICAL:\n- Prefer toBeVisible() for element checks, toContainText() for text, regex toHaveURL() for URLs\n- NEVER use toBeTruthy() on textContent()/getAttribute()/innerText() — they return null when element is missing\n- WRONG: const text = await el.textContent(); expect(text).toBeTruthy()\n- RIGHT: await expect(el).toBeVisible() or await expect(el).toContainText(/expected/)\n- Available expect matchers: toBe, toEqual, toBeTruthy, toBeFalsy, toContain, toMatch, toHaveURL, toHaveTitle, toBeVisible, toBeHidden, toHaveText, toContainText, toHaveAttribute, toHaveCount, toBeEnabled, toBeDisabled, toBeChecked, toHaveValue (all support .not)\n\nBEFORE writing page.goto(), verify the URL is in the available routes list above. If no route matches, use the closest parent route.\n\nReturn ONLY the code block, no explanations.`);\n\n  return parts.join('\\n');\n}\n\nexport function extractCodeFromResponse(response: string): string {","numLines":50,"startLine":720,"totalLines":804}}}
