{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BYAi1a1QGyLxcHEa9JqtWU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The runner tracks network failures (status >= 400 responses). When `networkErrorMode` is not 'ignore', they're added to `errorParts` which causes the test to fail.\n\nBut I can't modify the runner. The issue is that the server is returning 500 on `/`, `/record`, and `/review`. This could be a transient server issue during the Play Agent run, or it could be that these routes genuinely fail.\n\nLet me check if `/record` and `/review` work now:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1111,"cache_read_input_tokens":127511,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1111},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"2a016314-7229-410c-a149-f6a31bcb2137"}
