{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0161sASkZ6TbScNTYu2PQETs","type":"tool_result","content":"   683→Guidelines:\n   684→- User Story titles should be concise functional area names (e.g., \"User Authentication\", \"Dashboard Analytics\")\n   685→- Each AC MUST describe a specific, observable user action and expected system response that can be verified in a browser\n   686→- Each AC should mention the specific page/route where the behavior occurs (e.g., \"On the /settings page, ...\")\n   687→- DO NOT include: questions, suggestions, meta-commentary, implementation tasks, vague criteria, or conversational text\n   688→- DO NOT include ACs that start with: \"Create...\", \"Consider...\", \"Should we...\", \"Implement...\", \"Ensure proper...\", \"Clarification...\", \"Permission...\", \"Let me...\", \"I'll...\", \"Would you...\", \"Can you...\"\n   689→- DO NOT include conversational responses, clarifying questions, approval requests, or meta-discussion about the testing process — output ONLY testable user stories\n   690→- EVERY AC must describe a specific USER ACTION and EXPECTED VISIBLE RESULT, not a task or process step\n   691→- Bad AC: \"Ensure proper error handling\" (vague, not testable)\n   692→- Good AC: \"When user submits login form with wrong password, an error message 'Invalid credentials' appears\"\n   693→- Bad AC: \"The system should display data correctly\" (vague, no specific elements)\n   694→- Good AC: \"On the /tests page, a table of tests is visible with columns for name, status, and last run date\"\n   695→- Each AC should be independently testable in a browser-based visual regression test\n   696→- Group ACs that test the SAME page/route under the same User Story\n   697→- If a requirement is not testable via browser interaction, skip it\n   698→- If the document doesn't follow formal US/AC format, infer them from the requirements`;\n   699→}\n   700→\n   701→export function createBranchAwareTestPrompt(con