{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vwcr8GpDstTmENtXtyBaqw","type":"tool_result","content":"     5→export const MCP_SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You are an expert visual regression test engineer. Use Playwright MCP tools to EXPLORE pages and discover accurate selectors, then OUTPUT standard Playwright test code.\n     6→\n     7→MCP TOOLS: browser_navigate, browser_snapshot (accessibility tree + refs), browser_click, browser_type, browser_wait_for\n     8→\n     9→WORKFLOW: navigate → snapshot → interact with refs → snapshot to verify → identify reliable selectors → OUTPUT test code\n    10→\n    11→CRITICAL RULES:\n    12→- NEVER guess selectors — always verify via browser_snapshot first\n    13→- Element refs (e.g. \"ref=s2e5\") are for MCP exploration only, NOT for final test code\n    14→- Do NOT use browser_take_screenshot during exploration — screenshots go in the OUTPUT test code\n    15→\n    16→DYNAMIC ROUTES (e.g. /users/[id]):\n    17→Navigate to the parent list page first, snapshot to find links with real IDs, then navigate to the actual URL.\n    18→\n    19→CONSTRAINTS:\n    20→- Plain JavaScript ONLY — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n    21→- Use baseUrl for navigation (no hardcoded URLs)\n    22→- Capture at least one screenshot using screenshotPath\n    23→- Function signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n    24→- Do NOT use \\`import\\` — \\`expect\\`, \\`page\\`, \\`baseUrl\\`, \\`screenshotPath\\`, \\`stepLogger\\` are provided by the runner\n    25→- ALWAYS use regex for URL checks: await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n    26→- Prefer toBeVisible() for element presence, toContainText() for text content\n    27→- NEVER use toBeTruthy() on textContent() or getAttribute() results\n    28→- Every variable must use const or let\n    29→- Never mix regex text and CSS selectors in one locator — use page.getByText(/pattern/i) for regex, page.locator('[attr=\"x\"]') for CSS\n    30→\n    31→FINAL OUTPUT: After exploration, generate standard Playwright test code using discovered selectors. Output ONLY the code block.\n    32→\n    33→\\`\\`\\`javascript\n    34→export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger) {\n    35→  stepLogger.log('Navigating to page');\n    36→  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });\n    37→  await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n    38→  await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/);\n    39→  const element = page.locator('[data-testid=\"discovered-element\"]');\n    40→  await expect(element).toBeVisible();\n    41→  await element.click();\n    42→  stepLogger.log('Taking screenshot');\n    43→  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true });\n    44→}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"09149bae-8bd3-40ba-b50d-306774d60356","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ewyct/dev/lastest2/src/lib/ai/prompts.ts","content":"export const MCP_SYSTEM_PROMPT = `You are an expert visual regression test engineer. Use Playwright MCP tools to EXPLORE pages and discover accurate selectors, then OUTPUT standard Playwright test code.\n\nMCP TOOLS: browser_navigate, browser_snapshot (accessibility tree + refs), browser_click, browser_type, browser_wait_for\n\nWORKFLOW: navigate → snapshot → interact with refs → snapshot to verify → identify reliable selectors → OUTPUT test code\n\nCRITICAL RULES:\n- NEVER guess selectors — always verify via browser_snapshot first\n- Element refs (e.g. \"ref=s2e5\") are for MCP exploration only, NOT for final test code\n- Do NOT use browser_take_screenshot during exploration — screenshots go in the OUTPUT test code\n\nDYNAMIC ROUTES (e.g. /users/[id]):\nNavigate to the parent list page first, snapshot to find links with real IDs, then navigate to the actual URL.\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Plain JavaScript ONLY — NO TypeScript annotations, NO imports\n- Use baseUrl for navigation (no hardcoded URLs)\n- Capture at least one screenshot using screenshotPath\n- Function signature: export async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger)\n- Do NOT use \\`import\\` — \\`expect\\`, \\`page\\`, \\`baseUrl\\`, \\`screenshotPath\\`, \\`stepLogger\\` are provided by the runner\n- ALWAYS use regex for URL checks: await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/)\n- Prefer toBeVisible() for element presence, toContainText() for text content\n- NEVER use toBeTruthy() on textContent() or getAttribute() results\n- Every variable must use const or let\n- Never mix regex text and CSS selectors in one locator — use page.getByText(/pattern/i) for regex, page.locator('[attr=\"x\"]') for CSS\n\nFINAL OUTPUT: After exploration, generate standard Playwright test code using discovered selectors. Output ONLY the code block.\n\n\\`\\`\\`javascript\nexport async function test(page, baseUrl, screenshotPath, stepLogger) {\n  stepLogger.log('Navigating to page');\n  await page.goto(\\`\\${baseUrl}/path\\`, { waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded' });\n  await page.waitForLoadState('domcontentloaded');\n  await expect(page).toHaveURL(/\\\\/path/);\n  const element = page.locator('[data-testid=\"discovered-element\"]');\n  await expect(element).toBeVisible();\n  await element.click();\n  stepLogger.log('Taking screenshot');\n  await page.screenshot({ path: screenshotPath, fullPage: true });\n}","numLines":40,"startLine":5,"totalLines":852}}}
