{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019pTQsTUQ2uwwSRZVfoxFb6","type":"tool_result","content":"   657→\n   658→Return ONLY the JSON object inside a code block, no other text.`;\n   659→}\n   660→\n   661→export function createUserStoryExtractionPrompt(specContent: string): string {\n   662→  return `You are a strict parser. Extract User Stories and Acceptance Criteria from the document below. Output ONLY the structured markdown format shown — NO questions, NO clarifications, NO conversation, NO meta-commentary.\n   663→\n   664→Document content:\n   665→${specContent}\n   666→\n   667→Extract User Stories and Acceptance Criteria with the following rules:\n   668→1. Each distinct feature or capability should be its own User Story\n   669→2. Each User Story should have clear, testable Acceptance Criteria\n   670→3. Group related ACs under the same User Story\n   671→4. Provide a descriptive name for each AC that works as a test name\n   672→\n   673→Format your response as markdown using this exact structure:\n   674→\n   675→### User Story 1: [Functional area name]\n   676→**As a** [role]\n   677→**I want to** [feature/capability]\n   678→**So that** [benefit/value]\n   679→\n   680→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   681→- AC1: [Clear, testable criterion that describes expected behavior]\n   682→- AC2: [Another criterion]\n   683→\n   684→### User Story 2: [Next functional area]\n   685→...\n   686→\n   687→Guidelines:\n   688→- User Story titles should be concise functional area names (e.g., \"User Authentication\", \"Dashboard Analytics\")\n   689→- Each AC MUST describe a specific, observable user action and expected system response that can be verified in a browser\n   690→- Each AC should mention the specific page/route where the behavior occurs (e.g., \"On the /settings page, ...\")\n   691→- DO NOT include: questions, suggestions, meta-commentary, implementation tasks, vague criteria, or conversational text\n   692→- DO NOT include ACs that start with: \"Create...\", \"Consider...\", \"Should we...\", \"Implement...\", \"Ensure proper...\", \"Clarification...\", \"Permission...\", \"Let me...\", \"I'll...\", \"Would you...\", \"Can you...\"\n   693→- DO NOT include conversational responses, clarifying questions, approval requests, or meta-discussion about the testing process — output ONLY testable user stories\n   694→- EVERY AC must describe a specific USER ACTION and EXPECTED VISIBLE RESULT, not a task or process step\n   695→- Bad AC: \"Ensure proper error handling\" (vague, not testable)\n   696→- Good AC: \"When user submits login form with wrong password, an error message 'Invalid credentials' appears\"\n   697→- Bad AC: \"The system should display data correctly\" (vague, no specific elements)\n   698→- Good AC: \"On the /tests page, a table of tests is visible with columns for name, status, and last run date\"\n   699→- Each AC should be independently testable in a browser-based visual regression test\n   700→- Group ACs that test the SAME page/route under the same User Story\n   701→- If a requirement is not testable via browser interaction, skip it\n   702→- If the document doesn't follow formal US/AC format, infer them from the requirements\n   703→- QUALITY CHECK: Before outputting, verify each AC has a clear GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure or equivalent. Delete any AC that is a question, a request for permission, or meta-discussion about what to test`;\n   704→}"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"616c3e3f-f28a-4eda-8ff4-72bb8dd83484","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/ewyct/dev/lastest2/src/lib/ai/prompts.ts","content":"\nReturn ONLY the JSON object inside a code block, no other text.`;\n}\n\nexport function createUserStoryExtractionPrompt(specContent: string): string {\n  return `You are a strict parser. Extract User Stories and Acceptance Criteria from the document below. Output ONLY the structured markdown format shown — NO questions, NO clarifications, NO conversation, NO meta-commentary.\n\nDocument content:\n${specContent}\n\nExtract User Stories and Acceptance Criteria with the following rules:\n1. Each distinct feature or capability should be its own User Story\n2. Each User Story should have clear, testable Acceptance Criteria\n3. Group related ACs under the same User Story\n4. Provide a descriptive name for each AC that works as a test name\n\nFormat your response as markdown using this exact structure:\n\n### User Story 1: [Functional area name]\n**As a** [role]\n**I want to** [feature/capability]\n**So that** [benefit/value]\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- AC1: [Clear, testable criterion that describes expected behavior]\n- AC2: [Another criterion]\n\n### User Story 2: [Next functional area]\n...\n\nGuidelines:\n- User Story titles should be concise functional area names (e.g., \"User Authentication\", \"Dashboard Analytics\")\n- Each AC MUST describe a specific, observable user action and expected system response that can be verified in a browser\n- Each AC should mention the specific page/route where the behavior occurs (e.g., \"On the /settings page, ...\")\n- DO NOT include: questions, suggestions, meta-commentary, implementation tasks, vague criteria, or conversational text\n- DO NOT include ACs that start with: \"Create...\", \"Consider...\", \"Should we...\", \"Implement...\", \"Ensure proper...\", \"Clarification...\", \"Permission...\", \"Let me...\", \"I'll...\", \"Would you...\", \"Can you...\"\n- DO NOT include conversational responses, clarifying questions, approval requests, or meta-discussion about the testing process — output ONLY testable user stories\n- EVERY AC must describe a specific USER ACTION and EXPECTED VISIBLE RESULT, not a task or process step\n- Bad AC: \"Ensure proper error handling\" (vague, not testable)\n- Good AC: \"When user submits login form with wrong password, an error message 'Invalid credentials' appears\"\n- Bad AC: \"The system should display data correctly\" (vague, no specific elements)\n- Good AC: \"On the /tests page, a table of tests is visible with columns for name, status, and last run date\"\n- Each AC should be independently testable in a browser-based visual regression test\n- Group ACs that test the SAME page/route under the same User Story\n- If a requirement is not testable via browser interaction, skip it\n- If the document doesn't follow formal US/AC format, infer them from the requirements\n- QUALITY CHECK: Before outputting, verify each AC has a clear GIVEN/WHEN/THEN structure or equivalent. Delete any AC that is a question, a request for permission, or meta-discussion about what to test`;\n}","numLines":48,"startLine":657,"totalLines":853}}}
