{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VCTEr9Prg15QtkL4149pyR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The regex `(?:typescript|ts|javascript|js)?` — the `?` makes the language tag optional. So `` ```\\n `` (no language) is matched. Good.\n\nBut what about `` ```text\\n `` or `` ```plaintext\\n ``? These would NOT match because `text` isn't in the list. If the AI outputs code in a `text` block, it wouldn't be extracted. Let me make the regex more permissive:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":281,"cache_read_input_tokens":206722,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":281},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec911d5a-d516-40b8-8771-7468f6b1ba97","uuid":"06c4164e-6044-4e7b-a5f6-12dcdd6ec01e"}
